se to take part in Spanish class and thus provide unusually raw feedback on their teachers and classes. The engagement and resistance of these students suggests pedagogical directions for engaging Spanish heritage language learners. The book will be of interest to scholars, administrators, students and teachers involved in the delivery and assessment of heritage language classes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aHeritage language speakersxEducation (Secondary) 0aHeritage language speakersxEducation (Secondary). 0aMexican AmericansxEducation (Secondary)zUnited States. 0aSpanish languagexStudy and teaching (Secondary) 0aSpanish languagexStudy and teaching (Secondary). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aCharter Schools.  aEngaging Latinx learners.  aEthnographic research.  aHigh school teaching.  aLanguage maintenance and acquisition.  aLanguage pedagogy.  aPlace-based Pedagogy.  aSpanish as a heritage language.  aclassroom engagement.  aspanish heritage language.  astudent engagement.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishz978311070476108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020z9783110704563oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068960008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178892764240uhttps://www.degruyter.c